'''Angus MacInnes''' ([[October 27]], [[1940s#1947|1947]] &ndash; [[December 23]], [[2024]]) was a Canadian actor who played [[Jon Vander|Gold Leader]] in ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'' and [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

==Biography==
MacInnes was born in Windsor, Ontario, Canada on [[October 27]], [[1940s|1947]].<ref name="NYPost" />

In 1977 MacInnes appeared [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], as the Y-wing pilot Gold Leader. Although the character is only identified by his call sign and the nickname "Dutch" in the film, he was later given a full name, Jon Vander.

Archive footage of MacInnes was used in ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'', again showing him as Gold Leader. MacInnes also recorded additional lines for the film, including the line "Keep it tight and watch out for those towers."<ref name="Rogue One Return">{{YouTube|video=Oy--g2NjP7M|text=Star Wars 'Gold Leader' Actor on his Rogue One Return!|channel=channel/UCKhZplFZ1QaLqA_fCTVlU_g|name=Jamie Stangroom|archivedate=20201013215215}}</ref>

MacInnes passed away on [[December 23]], [[2024]], at the age of 77.<ref name="NYPost" />

